                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_cʼæǧæʒ" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><form type="lemma"><orth>cʼæǧæʒ</orth></form><usg><lang/></usg><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>челнок в ткацком станке</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>loom shuttle</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>шпулька швейной машины</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>bobbin of sewing machine</q></tr></sense></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Несомненная связь с <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/> <w>čʼäǧišk</w> <gloss><q>задвижка</q></gloss></mentioned> и возможная с <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>səǧəs</w> <gloss><q>клин</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>IV 620</biblScope></bibl>). Если допустить, что в исходной среде существовал перебой %iǧ%i || %iv%i (ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cigon"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ciwan"/> ‘чугун’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_suǧaq"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sovaq"/> ‘сайгак’ и др.), то мы можем восстановить параллельную форму *%icavac%i, которая окажется весьма близкой к <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(арханг.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(Arkhangelsk) </note><w>цывца</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>цевка</w> <gloss><q>шпулька</q></gloss></mentioned>, . К осетинскому %icʼæǧæʒ%i примыкает <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(мохев.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(Mokhevian) </note><w>čʼaǧačʼaj</w> <gloss><q>шпулька</q></gloss></mentioned> [<bibl><author>С. Макалатия</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Хеви, стр. 88 (на груз. яз.)</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Khevi, p. 88 (in Georgian)</biblScope></bibl>].</etym><etym xml:lang="en">There is a doubtless connection with <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/> <w>čʼäǧišk</w> <gloss><q>locking bar</q></gloss></mentioned> and a probable connection with <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>səǧəs</w> <gloss><q>wedge</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>IV 620</biblScope></bibl>). If we assume that there was an original change pattern %iǧ%i || %iv%i (cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cigon"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ciwan"/> ‘cast iron’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_suǧaq"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sovaq"/> ‘saiga’ etc.), then we can reconstruct a parallel form *%icavac%i which would be quite close to <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(арханг.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(Arkhangelsk) </note><w>цывца</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>цевка</w> <gloss><q>bobbin</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The following word <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(мохев.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(Mokhevian) </note><w>čʼaǧačʼaj</w> <gloss><q>шпулька</q></gloss></mentioned> [<bibl><author>S. Makalatia.</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Хеви, стр. 88 (на груз. яз.)</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Khevi, p. 88 (in Georgian)</biblScope></bibl>] relates to the Ossetic %icʼæǧæʒ%i.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>